==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: impish
<hw>imp"ish</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧mp"⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
the qualities, or showing the characteristics, of an imp; naughtily or
annoyingly playful; <as>as, teasing and worrying with <ex>impish</ex>
laughter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> elfish, elvish, implike, mischievous, pixilated,
prankish, puckish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impishly</ent>⟦br⟧
